Meriden contains several old buildings of particular interest, the majority of them are situated away from the present centre of the village and are clustered around the Church about a mile away on high land to the south-east just outside our area. These buildings form the{Meriden Hill {Conservation Area.}
Within the village itself lies{The {Bulls Head Inn, }which is now a restaurant. It was formerly a coaching inn on the main Birmingham to Holyhead road, and was used as a staging post for changing horses before the climb up Meriden Hill.
There are also several thatched properties to be found in and around the village.
